-- Cavaliers Owner Gilbert Gets $100,000 Fine for Comments About LeBron James
-- Erik Matuszewski
-- 2010-07-13T01:53:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-13/cavaliers-owner-gilbert-gets-100-000-fine-for-comments-about-lebron-james.html

          
          
             Cleveland Cavaliers owner  Dan Gilbert  was fined $100,000 by the National Basketball
Association for his comments about  LeBron James , who left
Cleveland to join the Miami Heat.  
 NBA Commissioner  David Stern  disclosed the fine during the
league’s owners meetings in Las Vegas.  
 Gilbert called James’s decision, which was disclosed during
a nationally televised program, a “shameful display of
selfishness and betrayal.”  
